l tensor ready for ResNet50:\n\n1. Compute log-mel spectrogram with `librosa` (`N_MELS` bins)\n2. Normalise to [0, 255] (uint8)\n3. Stack the single channel three times to form a fake-RGB image\n4. Resize to `IMG_SIZE x IMG_SIZE` (224x224) using the ImageNet transform pipeline\n5. Apply ImageNet mean/std normalisation\n\nThe `train_transform` adds a small random horizontal flip to the spectrogram image\nas an additional augmentation (left-right flip = small time shift).","metadata":{}},{"id":"615991cf-fe14-49e1-86b5-56fbe5e5bfe9","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── CELL 14: audio_to_melspec ──────────────────────────\nfrom PIL import Image\n\nIMAGENET_MEAN = [0.485, 0.456, 0.406]\nIMAGENET_STD  = [0.229, 0.224, 0.225]\n\nbase_transform = transforms.Compose([\n    transforms.Resize((IMG_SIZE, IMG_SIZE)),\n    transforms.ToTensor(),\n    transforms.Normalize(mean=IMAGENET_MEAN, std=IMAGENET_STD),\n])\n\ntrain_transform = transforms.Compose([\n    transforms.Resize((IMG_SIZE, IMG_SIZE)),\n    transforms.RandomHorizontalFlip(p=0.5),\n    transforms.ToTensor(),\n    transforms.Normalize(mean=IMAGENET_MEAN, std=IMAGENET_STD),\n])\n\n# torchaudio transforms are faster than librosa on CPU (C++ backend, no GIL overhead)\n_mel_transform = torchaudio.transforms.MelSpectrogram(\n    sample_rate = SAMPLE_RATE,\n    n_fft       = 2048,\n    hop_length  = 512,\n    n_mels      = N_MELS,\n    f_max       = 8000,\n)\n_db_transform = torchaudio.transforms.AmplitudeToDB(top_db=80)\n\n\ndef audio_to_melspec(audio: np.ndarray, transform=base_transform) -> torch.Tensor:\n    waveform = torch.from_numpy(audio).unsqueeze(0)          # (1, T)\n    mel_db   = _db_transform(_mel_transform(waveform))       # (1, N_MELS, T')\n    mel_db   = mel_db.squeeze(0).numpy()                     # (N_MELS, T')\n    mel_norm = ((mel_db - mel_db.min()) / (mel_db.max() - mel_db.min() + 1e-6) * 255).astype(np.uint8)\n    rgb      = np.stack([mel_norm, mel_norm, mel_norm], axis=2)\n    img      = Image.fromarray(rgb, mode='RGB')\n    return transform(img)\n\n\nprint('audio_to_melspec ready! (torchaudio backend)')\n","metadata":{},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["audio_to_melspec ready! (torchaudio backend)\n"]}],"execution_count":10},{"id":"ebdb7094-faf0-4d3b-8f7f-4b9ffa6bcfee","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Cell 15 — ResNet50 Model Definition\n\n`GenreClassifier` wraps the pretrained ResNet50 backbone and replaces the default\n1000-class head with a custom 10-class head:\n\n`Linear(2048->512) -> BatchNorm1d(512) -> ReLU -> Dropout(0.5) -> Linear(512->10)`\n\nBackbone layers are exposed as explicit attributes (`self.layer1` ... `self.layer4`)\nso the training loops can freeze/unfreeze them by name without relying on fragile\nindex-based access.","metadata":{}},{"id":"322f4609-23d1-4fae-91cf-4efec2bb350f","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── CELL 15: GenreClassifier (ResNet50) ────────────────\nclass GenreClassifier(nn.Module):\n    \"\"\"ResNet50 backbone with a custom 10-class head for genre classification.\n\n    Args:\n        num_classes: Number of output classes (default: 10)\n        pretrained:  Load ImageNet weights (default: True)\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, num_classes: int = 10, pretrained: bool = True):\n        super().__init__()\n        weights  = models.ResNet50_Weights.IMAGENET1K_V2 if pretrained else None\n        backbone = models.resnet50(weights=weights)\n\n        # expose individual stage attributes for granular freeze control\n        self.conv1   = backbone.conv1\n        self.bn1     = backbone.bn1\n        self.relu    = backbone.relu\n        self.maxpool = backbone.maxpool\n        self.layer1  = backbone.layer1\n        self.layer2  = backbone.layer2\n        self.layer3  = backbone.layer3\n        self.layer4  = backbone.layer4\n        self.avgpool = backbone.avgpool\n\n        self.fc = nn.Sequential(\n            nn.Linear(2048, 512),\n            nn.BatchNorm1d(512),\n            nn.ReLU(),\n       